<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">greywolffe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I know this has been discussed in the past but wanted to relate a story.<P>In KC the other day (not a train story).  I hear in /ooc "Ressing for donations at zone."  I don't think much about it and continue playing for awhile but soon leave to go restock in FV.<P>In Dreadlands and hear again /ooc "Ressing for donations at zone."  I do a /who and this person is anon.  So being the sarcastic cleric I am I /ooc "Rezzing for free."  Now here's where it gets funny.<P>Anon-cleric "Bah, only a 49 res."<BR>Me "So what, at least they don't have to pay."<BR>Anon-cleric "*rollseyes*"<BR>NonAnon-cleric "Ressing for free."  <P>Did a slash /who on this new response and it's a level 60.  I laugh hard at that and the fact that anon-cleric was no longer in the zone.<P>I'm not attempting to flame the anon-cleric but I don't like "demanding" money for rezzes.  It peeves me that everytime I ask someone if they *want* a rez they all ask me "how much will it cost?"  I didn't ask them to *pay* for the rez, just if they *wanted* it.  <P>I seldom accept cash for rezzing people but have yet to turn down an item (peridots) or any type of alcoholic beverage.   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/biggrin.gif">  Best way to get me to rez you is carry an extra stack of Elven Wine with you.  (Almost have drinking tolerance maxxed).<P><P>------------------<BR>Greywolffe Silverstarr<BR>53rd Cleric of Tunare<BR>E'Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tundar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Spoken by a true elf, I've been maxed in drinking since around L40 or so   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/tongue.gif"><P>I tend to shout: Rezzing at "insert whatever place I'm at".<BR>If I have the time to rez, it's sure is for free (unless I have to go from DL to Dalnir   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"> )<P><--- is (of course) a dwarf<p>[This message has been edited by Tundar (edited 06-14-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jaldarith</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">/IMO [on]<P>You're like me, greywolffe.  I absolutely hate seeing Clerics shout "ressing for donations" in zones.  There are so many other things you can do to get rich from, than sucking the money out of the unfortunate people.<P>Whenever I ressurect somebody and run off after I heal/buff them, they ALWAYS ask me how much it is- nothing bothers me more than that...  All the Clerics of the past always charged for ressurects, and I don't see why.  Sure, I can see donations, but why *CHARGE* ???<P>I always tell them it's free, and they freak out!  They're like "THANKS YOU ROCK!!!!!!!" and it's crazy as heck.  NOBODY should have to pay for a ressurect- regardless if it's 700 mana or not.  Sit on your arse for 3 minutes and get it all back, sheesh.<P>I'll cancel all donations unless they're persistant.  From my level 49-57 life span, I've probably accepted about 200pp total in ressurection donations.  If I charged ...say... 100pp for all my ressurects, I would have about 90k platinum.<P>/IMO [off]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Darus Grey</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You dont even have to shout for donations.<BR>People will just hand you 50-200pp anyways<BR>Will I take it? hell yeah<BR>We're Clerics, in general, we're poor.<BR>Every little bit counts<BR>Druids, Wizards, Shamans, etc have little to no hangups about charging for ports/buffs.<P>Why should we about something that is much more helpful and in demand.....</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aordolar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I really don’t understand the logic behind this.  What is the big deal he’s probably low on cash and needs the PP.  I mean look at the Druids, I spent lots of money getting ports and its just a little port it doesn’t get me any XP back.  Druids make a killing off of ports and I never see anyone bitching about that.  I tried to get an evac to SF last night and the guy wanted a 100pp.  Talk about extortion!  <P>Personally I never ask of donations in ooc or shout but when I res someone I tell them up front, for donation and the donation given should reflect your level because I just saved you many hours of play.  If I am full mana and the res will not affect my group as far as waiting for me to med then I res for free.<P>I am well know for doing fly by res’s for free and traveling for res’s when bored or just trying to figure out what I am going to do that night.  So lots of the times I don’t expect or even ask for PP.<P>But I really don’t think you should mess with someone trying to make some cash.<P>Just my 2 cents.<P>Aordolar hides behibd the tree.<P>------------------<BR>Aordolar Trueheal<BR>53th Season Drunken Cleric of Brell<BR>Dark Vigilance<BR>Innoruuk Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Meddik</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I never demanded donations, if the corpse is near me.<P>And if its not near me, (I.E. I gotta run more than about 100 feet to get to it) They had better throw a cash offer into the initial request, or I'm probably gonna be too busy. Heck, in many many cases, even for money I'm too busy.<P>Now if the corpse is brought to me, they can ahve a res for free. If they offer a donation, I'd never turn it down.<P>If they ask how much they owe me, I jsut tell them "Whatever the XP restored is worth to you."<P>But I don't go around like someone selling Peanuts and Beers at a Ballgame hawking my wares.<P>------------------<BR>Meddik Sawbones<BR>Member of <A HREF="http://www.suvangi.com/drunkenbandits/" TARGET=_blank>Drunken Bandits</A><BR>(Bristlebane Server)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Naida-Brell</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Here is my problem with "Rezzing for donations" or <b>anything</b> "for donations". Good god almighty would you people use a dictionary? A donation is a <b>voluntary</b> thing. If you demand it, it's not a donation.<P>If you want to charge for donations, I don't care. That's not my way but you're not me. But...be honest about it!<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Wisecleric</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Naida-Brell<BR>"Here is my problem with "Rezzing for donations" or anything "for donations". Good god almighty would you people use a dictionary? A donation is a voluntary thing. If you demand it, it's not a donation.<BR>If you want to charge for donations, I don't care. That's not my way but you're not me. But...be honest about it!"<P>I kind of look at it like that little blue box of different colored peppermints by the cash register. <P>You don't HAVE to put any change in there to take one. But if you would like to leave a donation you are more than welcome. Also you might feel a tad guility if you have change in your pocket and don't put it in the box.<P>So every time a see someone shout ressing for donations, i think of that little blue box of peppermints.  <P>Oh, btw, last week i went from Kael to SS (where im non-KOS) and did a res for 500 plat. Heh, largest payment so far. (<--i consider it a payment since he gave me a tell right off saying "ill give you 500 plat to come to SS and res me".)<BR> </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
